A CounterStrike.Source Map by La Gare

Thanks for downloading my first map! Hope you like!

The .bsp and the .nav file go in the following directory

C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\"YOUR STEAM ID/NAME"\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

and the .cache file goes in the soundcache folder

C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\"YOUR STEAM ID/NAME"\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps\soundcache

When you've extracted them to their correct directories you're ready to go!

Oh! And a little tip, the boat on the map...like any boat on cs.s has some issues, drive slowly at first!
The steering wheel is the ignition. It's set to start on touch AND on use so either walk into the 
steering wheel or press e on it. It does sometimes have problems, but be persistant it will start!

Enjoy! And thanks again for downloading!


La Gare

This map is highly planned and detailed, having multiple pathways to the two bomb sites complete with optional paths to every area, perfect to test out your strategy.


This map comes complete with:


-Highly polished graphics, with all the bells and whistles from moving overhead clouds to crisp skylight shadows

-Smooth frame-rate in all areas with the use of Hint brushes
-Environmental based audio for all areas

-Strategically placed explosive barrels to weaken the enemy before attacking

-Timed meeting points for optimum game-play

-Bot support (being improved for final release)

-Great Z-action (The use of height to gain advantage on a player) with the use of overhanging catwalks

-Fun game-play and support for any number of players, from 4-32!

Hope you download and enjoy!

NOW FIXED FOR ORANGE BOX UPDATE! ===================================
DE_VEGAS\_LITE (FOR LARGE SERVERS)
===================================
- This is a LITE version of de\_vegas\_css which allows for up to 64 players. - The full version of this map can only support up to 32 players due to entity lists reaching their capacity. - In order to make the map compatible with 64 players, minor physics props have been removed (such as hanging pictures on the walls) and the lighting effects have been greatly recuded throughout the map. - If your server is LARGER than 32 slots, use this version of the map. Otherwise, use the full version called "de_vegas\_css". ===================================
Author: SM Sith Lord
Email: smsithlord@yahoo.com
Website: http://www.engport.net Description:
THIS IS THE LITE VERSION OF THE MAP, meaning a good portion of the lighting effects and minor props (such as hanging pictures) have been removed to allow for 64 working spawn points without crashing the server. The complete version of this map is called de\_vegas\_css and is recommended for no more than 32 player servers or less. These maps are remakes of the original old 1.X map de\_vegas (original credits below). Stayed true to the original layout. Nearly all the old angles are still there. Changed a few secrets, and added a few more. Most changes to the map are purely visual. Islamic extremists have targeted Sin City for their next strike against the American way of life. Hoping to further cripple the US economy, a string of attacks have been coordinated and executed in the fabulous city of Las Vegas, Nevada. The intensity of the strikes increase as the CT's initial response teams quickly become overwhelmed, effectively turning Las Vegas into a war zone. Your squad has been assigned to respond to an unidentified helicopter landing at the High Times Hotel & Casino, the sight of an earlier attack which claimed the lives of several of your fellow agents. Homeland Security has identified the strike and confirmed that the terrorist have two probable objectives that they are likely to attempt to destroy. Target A: As a moral statement, the terrorists have been detonating bombs at strip clubs across the city all night. It is suspected that the High Times Lounge will be the next club to be hit. The club is identifiable by the large Sphinx statue outside of its entrance. Target B: The previous attack at this location was a failed effort to empty the casino's vault. It is probable that this second attack is an attempt to finish the job. Allowing the terrorists to escape the scene with the funds is unacceptable. Secure & hold the vault! Additional Credits:
All the beta testers on the [DoP] High Times server for finding & putting up with all the terrible bugs & giving valuable feedback. [DoP] Vulgar for letting all that happen. All the people from other forums that helped me fix those bugs (FPSBanana, Interlopers). The authors of GMOW v3 Solid\_Granite, GiGaBiTe. All the creators of the original de\_vegas. And, lastly, VALVE for creating a sweet game/engine/resources that I could work with. Original Map Credits:
Originally created by +Cadaver+, textures by George\_Pooshoes and JOeSmOe. Additional credits to Macman, Chaos, Tech3D, Jubilee, and Agent Orange. =====================
NAVIGATION FILE (.nav)
=====================
Credits for the .nav file go to chizbone. Special thanks to him for taking care of it for me. Download CSS .nav file for de\_vegas\_lite here.

Refer http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/52549

de_vast by DarkMortar
_____________________

This map takes place in a un-real city that contains
a refinery, a hotel, roads, and a overpass. This map supports 
32 players. This small and simple layout creates frantic fire-
fights within the dark tunnels and the outside of the hotel.

This level may cause quite a bit of lag and/or stress on the 
video card. It is recommended you lower your settings in 
intense multi-play. This map has bot support yet they do not 
use all the paths well and are predictable. They may also get 
stuck at the windows of the hotel.

This map also contains custom soundscapes which will make you feel like you are really there. 

Most of all, have fun.

DarkMortar.

Probably last map of my reconstruction project. 
We call this top of hill "kopec" which means hill in czech. There is ancient Watchtower build 100 years ago. There is also pub next to this sight. Little lower is abandoned pool, which become dilapidated.

I tried to make strategic experiment - make 3 bombsites on relative open and small area. All three bombsites are connected by underground halls and rooms.

Unfortunately, CSS don't count with 3 bombsites, so C doesn't appear on minimap. Bombsite area covers entire building so you can put bomb even on roof, if you can get there...

I learned soundscapes for this map, so atmosphere is quite better than in my recent maps. Next big step is my own models used in map. You may notice new cars. Those are part of my custom models pack. 

If you like this one, check all of my maps here
This map or its parts is also used in my singleplayer mod

Have a fun

This is the alpha of de_urbancollege_a1. Obviously, it is an large urban college in the middle of a city. This is dev textured of course, due to it being an alpha. Due to this being a 420 release, one of the bombsites is designed to reflect that. The other bomb site has a bunch of random nuclear waste. These are placeholders. I do plan on changing the bomb sites when I texture it and go on to the beta version, but I just wanted to include something more then just 'bomb site crates' for the time being. 

It is designed for 32-64 players and the map is very large with both indoor and outdoor combat. You can actually travel anywhere both indoors and outdoors and the map is easily large enough to have a good 64 player firefight without it being crowded.
Beta 2

This map was made for a LAN party where team work is key. This map feel is mid to close quarters combat, with many alternate routes so your team shouldn't get bottle necked.
    The T's spawn in a deserted under ground parking garage. And the CT's spawn in a small park. There are 2 bomb sites. One on a helicopter landing pad filled with crates. And the other in a small industrial building.
    The player can use the ground or climb on to cat walks for a height advantage.

This map was created by th3HAWKER. Have fun.

This is the updated, and much improved, version of Rage. The updates include two important glitch fixes and a major face lift. Urban takes you out of the Dev arena of Rage, and places you in an urban training zone, with construction, trees and even bushes to hide in. The lighting is by far my best, and the textures give the map an all-around green look. One of the glitches fixed was the ability to jump off the rooftop bombsite, and navigate along the outer walls along the map. This was fixed with the addition of taller walls. Another glitch fixed, was the water planting site. I noticed it was way too hard for the bots to plant/defuse with the ability to plant in the water, so I removed that. Other than those details, Urban remains nearly the same as Rage in geography, with a whole new color scheme and lighting effect.
